136 West 137th Street, south side, between Lenox and Seventh Avenues. This is a two-story frame house with a stucco front.

1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

West 137th Street, south side, between Lenox and Fifth Aves., showing the south wall of the 4-story ambulance station unit of Harlem Hospital, after the dismantlement of a 4-story glass veranda, which was attached to the building. The work was carried out with W.P.A. labor and funds, February 4, 1937.

W.P.A. Photo.
City Wide Project.

West 137th Street, south side, between Lenox and Fifth Aves., showing the 4-story ambulance station unit of Harlem Hospital, as seen from the interior ambulance driveway and yard.  January 6, 1937.  W.P.A. Photo.  City Wide Project.
